               <item n="m_philcomment_old">&lt;p&gt;Recto and verso cannot be determined. There may be a meter with a cola of seven syllables in b1 ff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a3.&lt;/b&gt; Here we have a quotation of Uv 30.11cd without direct translation. It is possible that the two preceding pādas were also quoted before.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a4.&lt;/b&gt; The Sanskrit is corrupt. One may venture to recognize &lt;i&gt;jala-bhujaga-&lt;/i&gt; ‘watersnake’. This word is recorded as variant of Skt. &lt;i&gt;uraga-&lt;/i&gt; ‘snake’ in a pāda repeated often in the Udānavarga (18.21d; 32.55-80).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a5.&lt;/b&gt; This may be part of a colophon composed in Sanskrit referring to a Kuchean king bearing the Sanskrit name Āryapūṣpa.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b2.&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;tallā= wnolme&lt;/i&gt; stands for &lt;i&gt;tallāw wnolme&lt;/i&gt; with sandhi (for &lt;i&gt;tallā&lt;sub&gt;u&lt;/sub&gt; onolme&lt;/i&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</item>
